{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dbf1adef-bbd5-4737-9fbd-5fdda035bdc7","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform with treenode filters. The command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nThe treenode filter path follows the structure `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`, so `/**/SmsNotificationTests/**` matches the class regardless of assembly/namespace and includes all tests within it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1cd8c667-5830-45ab-b06f-6b0a7de3e0a7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project (version 0.6.120). TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as its runner. For TUnit with MTP, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nTUnit uses a treenode filter syntax. To filter by class name, the syntax is:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nOr with the `--filter` option if it supports VSTest-style filters. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nTUnit 0.6.x uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The filter syntax for MTP with TUnit uses `--treenode-filter`. To filter by class:\n\n\nThe treenode filter path structure for TUnit follows the pattern `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`, so filtering by the class name `SmsNotificationTests` can be done with glob-like patterns using either `/**/SmsNotificationTests/**` or the more explicit `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` syntax.","outputTokens":489,"requestId":"BC55:22A1A7:2B6DF3:32D19B:69FA95FA"},"id":"45f48de8-6dea-4508-aa6a-da32ed0a5054","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:14:45.019Z","parentId":"6a79889d-f9ef-4294-b425-52927be9a693"}
